article.headline: North Carolina A&T 90, Florida A&M 82
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- Steven Rush scored a game-high 34 points, including seven 3-pointers, to lead North Carolina A&T to a 90-82 win over Florida A&M on Monday night. Austin Ewing scored 18 points and Trahern Chaplin added 12 for the Aggies (11-14, 7-6 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference), who led 46-30 at the break. Rush went 11-for-17 shooting and made 7-of-11 3-point attempts. The Aggies went 52.7 percent shooting and hit on 70.4 percent of free throws, while Florida A&M finished 44.3 percent shooting and 63 percent from the free throw line. Leslie Robinson's 23 points led four Florida A&M players in double digits. Brian Greene and Darius Glover each added 15 points for Florida A&M (14-12, 8-5 Mid-Eastern), and Ernest Maul had 12 points.
